Since opening our doors in 1947, MFS Investment Management Canada Limited has grown to become one of Canada’s most respected investment management companies. From offices in Toronto, Montréal, Vancouver and Chicago, we manage over $34 billion on behalf of pension, foundation & endowment, private wealth and mutual fund clients.
We take a team approach to investing, which allows our clients to take advantage of the collective strength of our various investment managers and analysts. We create separate teams that are comprised of three to seven individuals who build model portfolios for asset mix, Canadian equities (growth, value and core), global equities (growth, value and core), U.S. equities, EAFE (Europe, Australasia and Far East) equities and fixed income.
However, no team is ever complete without you, the client, as the decisions of each of our teams are implemented according to your investment objectives. This is why our portfolio managers stress the importance of regular meetings with you, so that we are constantly aware of all of your requirements and wishes.
MFS Investment Management Canada Limited’s success is based in large part on an entrepreneurial team culture. As owner-managers, we focus on running the business with a long term view and are strongly incented to maintain superior investment research, establish long-run succession planning, facilitate steady growth, and uphold the highest service standards. On a long-term basis, management owns 40% of the firm, with share ownership currently spread among 60 partners, and Sun Life Financial Corp. owning the balance. The MFS Investment Management Canada Limited team consists of over 110 employees, including 46 portfolio managers of whom 17 are research analysts.
To learn more about MFS Investment Management Canada Limited and how we would work together, please get in touch. We look forward to it.
Five areas distinguish MFS Investment Management Canada Limited:
Proven Investment Management Philosophy
Our firm uses a team-based majority voting approach to investment management. Decisions are made by experienced teams of investment managers supported by a globally oriented group of research analysts. This process integrates decision-making and research to maximize synergies regarding idea generation and portfolio structure.
Depth of our research expertise
The recognized research expertise within each of our investment management groups enables us to emphasize internal proprietary research in our investment process. Research is done on a global basis.
Equity Management Process
By using integrated equity management teams and structuring their responsibilities along global sectors, we have allowed every equity strategy to be managed on a truly global basis. All portfolios have focused approaches that have clearly defined risk controls.
Strong, Stable Organization and Ability to Effectively Handle Management Transition
We have an experienced management group, which is diversified by age. We are committed to having a management structure, which provides orderly personnel succession and is not overly dependent on any particular individual. The investment groups operate in a disciplined, democratic fashion while maintaining our long-term investment philosophy. We have been managing money successfully since 1947 and have demonstrated our ability to handle management changes.
Superior Service
Our client retention rate is high and, in part, this has been the result of the strong rapport we have built with plan sponsors and investment committees. Our investment reviews are structured to make our investment results and intentions clear and concise. We regularly consult with clients to ensure they are provided with the information they require.




























 


 



MFS McLean Budden Becomes MFS Investment Management Canada Limited | Business Wire
























































MFS McLean Budden Becomes MFS Investment Management Canada Limited




Name Change Demonstrates Local Commitment, Aligns with Global Brand






November 04, 2013 10:45 AM Eastern Standard Time



BOSTON & TORONTO--(BUSINESS WIRE)--Global asset manager MFS® has announced a name change to its Canadian 
      operations. MFS McLean Budden is now MFS Investment Management Canada 
      Limited. The name change reflects the consistency of the MFS brand 
      and aligns the Canadian division with MFS' global operations.
    


      "The Canadian market represents a key area of focus for MFS," said 
      Michael Roberge, MFS president and chief investment officer. “A local 
      presence is important to MFS. Our regional Canadian investment teams 
      help deliver real-time knowledge and insights to their MFS counterparts 
      around the world. That same approach employed globally by MFS in other 
      local markets enhances the knowledge and insights available to our 
      Canadian investment teams. They work collaboratively across sectors and 
      asset classes as part of 200-plus person investment team, to the benefit 
      of our clients globally.”
    

      In September 2011, MFS' parent company, Sun Life Financial, merged 
      McLean Budden with MFS, significantly increasing MFS' presence in 
      Canada. Today, MFS’ global research platform benefits from a team of 22 
      Canadian investment professionals based in Toronto offering local 
      investment insight, including trading, working collaboratively across 
      eight global sector teams. Client relations, sales, marketing, legal and 
      other operational functions are conducted in Toronto, Montreal and 
      Vancouver as well.
    

      "The new name extends the consistency of our brand identity and our 
      global approach," said Carol Geremia, president of MFS Institutional 
      Advisors, Inc. "In addition, it represents the importance MFS places on 
      its Canadian business and our inherent promise to deliver a world class 
      client experience that clients around the world have come to expect.”
    

      The name change took effect November 1, 2013. For more information, 
      visit the new Institutions & Consultants Web site for Canadian investors 
      on mfs.com.
    

About MFS Investment Management


      MFS is an active, global asset manager with investment offices in 
      Boston, Hong Kong, London, Mexico City, São Paulo, Singapore, Sydney, 
      Tokyo and Toronto. We employ a uniquely collaborative approach to build 
      better insights for our clients. Our investment approach has three core 
      elements of integrated research, global collaboration and active risk 
      management. Established in 1924, MFS manages US$385.6 billion in assets 
      on behalf of individual and institutional investors worldwide, as of 
      September 30, 2013. Please visit mfs.com for more information.
    

MFS Investment Management111 Huntington Avenue, Boston, 
      MA 02199


      29138.1
    


